hediston, East Suffolk, England":"英国英格兰素福爾可迪斯頓","Norfolk, England":"英国英格兰諾福爾可","lifeSummary":"William Claxton III, Esq于大约1400年出生在英国英格兰諾福爾可。他于1423年与Mary Browne在英国英格兰諾福爾可諾維其结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他去世于1500年在英国英格兰諾福爾可諾維其享年101岁。"},"hr":{"abt 1400–1500":"oko 1400.–1500.","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–preminula","1424–1502":"1424.–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500.","abt 1400":"oko 1400.","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424.","1423":"1423.","1500":"1500.","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Chediston, East Suffolk, England":"Chediston, Suffolk, Engleska, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"abt 1400–1500":"okolo 1400–1500","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–Zesnulá","1424–1502":"1424–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500","abt 1400":"okolo 1400","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Chediston, East Suffolk, England":"Chediston, Suffolk, Anglie, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"abt 1400–1500":"omkring 1400–1500","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–Afdød","1424–1502":"1424–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500","abt 1400":"omkring 1400","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Chediston, East Suffolk, England":"Chediston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"abt 1400–1500":"circa 1400–1500","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–Overleden","1424–1502":"1424–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500","abt 1400":"circa 1400","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Chediston, East Suffolk, England":"Chediston, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"abt 1400–1500":"about 1400–1500","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–Deceased","1424–1502":"1424–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500","abt 1400":"about 1400","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","Chediston, East Suffolk, England":"Chediston, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Claxton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places called Claxton, for example in County Durham, Norfolk, and Yorkshire, or from Long Clawson (Leicestershire). All are derived from an English genitive form of the Old Norse personal name <i>Klakkr</i> (see   Clack  ) + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘settlement’."],"variants":[{"name":"Clack","meanings":["English:","from the Old English personal name <i>Clacc</i> or its Old Norse (Danish) cognate <i>Klak</i>. As a personal name this is from a word meaning ‘lump’ and may have been used as a nickname for a large or thickset man.","possibly sometimes from a derivative of Middle English <i>clakken</i> ‘to rattle, clatter’, denoting a chatterer, alternatively, perhaps a miller, from the clack or clatter of his mill, or a bellringer."]},{"name":"Cluxton","meanings":["English: variant of   Claxton  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]},{"name":"Clawson","meanings":["English: variant of   Claxton  .","Americanized form of North German, Danish, and Norwegian   Clausen  ,   Claussen  , or   Klausen  , and also of their Dutch cognates, such as <b>Claassen</b> or <b>Klaassen</b>, patronymics from short forms of the local equivalents of the personal name   Nicholas  . Compare   Clauson  ."]},{"name":"Claxon","meanings":["English (Essex): variant of   Claxton  . This name is absent from the medieval record, and is therefore unlikely to be a patronymic from the medieval personal name <i>Clak</i> + <i>son</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Claxton III, Esq was born about 1400, in Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. He married Mary Browne in 1423, in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1500, in Norwich, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 101."},"et":{"abt 1400–1500":"umbes 1400–1500","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–Surnud","1424–1502":"1424–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500","abt 1400":"umbes 1400","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chediston, East Suffolk, England":"Chediston, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Norfolk, England":"Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1400–1500":"noin 1400–1500","1404–1502":"1404–1502","1404–Female":"1404–Kuollut","1424–1502":"1424–1502","1400–1500":"1400–1500","abt 1400":"noin 1400","1404":"1404","1502":"1502","1424":"1424","1423":"1423","1500":"1500","1400":"1400","Norwich, Norfolk, England":"Norwich, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kunin